description:
&lt;p&gt;The Royal Free London NHS Foundation Trust are recruiting an Endoscopy Decontamination Technician to work in their reprocessing facility in Enfield EN1 1TZ which opened in June 2019. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;This is an exciting and challenging role for a Technician who has an eye for detail and wants to provide a high quality decontamination service for the endoscopy unit. The role involves the decontamination and maintenance of all endoscopy scopes, the traceability and documentation of decontamination procedure and the reporting and returning of faulty endoscopic equipment. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;You will be given extensive internal and external training and benefit from being part of a team using the newest re-processing technology.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Working pattern: Wednesday to Sunday 08:00 to 16:00&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There will be a Numeracy and Literacy Screening Assessment before you are interviewed on the day.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name: Jason Cox&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title: Deputy General Manager&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address: jasoncox@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number: 0207 794 0500 x 54106&lt;/p&gt;
